1
00:00:00,798 --> 00:00:03,628
<i>Water.</i>

2
00:00:03,629 --> 00:00:05,773
<i>Earth.</i>

3
00:00:05,774 --> 00:00:08,412
<i>Fire.</i>

4
00:00:08,413 --> 00:00:10,383
<i>Air.</i>

5
00:00:11,365 --> 00:00:14,687
<i>My grandmother used to tell me stories about the old days.</i>

6
00:00:14,688 --> 00:00:16,326
<i>A time of peace.</i>

7
00:00:16,327 --> 00:00:20,183
<i>When the Avatar kept balance between the Water Tribes, Earth Kingdom,...</i>

8
00:00:20,184 --> 00:00:22,945
<i>...Fire Nation, and Air Nomads.</i>

9
00:00:22,946 --> 00:00:27,074
<i>But that all changed when the Fire Nation attacked.</i>

10
00:00:29,752 --> 00:00:33,286
<i>Only the Avatar mastered all four elements.</i>

11
00:00:33,287 --> 00:00:36,588
<i>Only he could stop the ruthless firebenders.</i>

12
00:00:36,589 --> 00:00:42,413
<i>But when the world needed him most, he vanished.</i>

13
00:00:42,891 --> 00:00:48,242
<i>A hundred years have passed and the Fire Nation is nearing victory in the war.</i>

14
00:00:48,243 --> 00:00:50,739
<i>Two years ago, my father and the men of my tribe...</i>

15
00:00:50,740 --> 00:00:54,116
<i>...journeyed to the Earth Kingdom to help fight against the Fire Nation.</i>

16
00:00:54,117 --> 00:00:58,072
<i>Leaving me and my brother to look after our tribe.</i>

17
00:00:58,073 --> 00:01:02,209
<i>Some people believe that the Avatar was never reborn into the Air Nomads.</i>

18
00:01:02,210 --> 00:01:06,306
<i>And that the cycle is broken, but I haven't lost hope.</i>

19
00:01:06,307 --> 00:01:12,154
<i>I still believe that somehow the Avatar will return to save the world.</i>

20
00:01:20,468 --> 00:01:23,721
Book One: Water
Chapter Two: The Avatar Returns

21
00:01:34,741 --> 00:01:37,580
Yay! Aang's back!

22
00:01:45,383 --> 00:01:48,993
I knew it! You signaled the Fire Navy with that flare!

23
00:01:48,994 --> 00:01:50,988
You're leading them straight to us, aren't you?

24
00:01:50,989 --> 00:01:53,910
Aang didn't do anything. It was an accident.

25
00:01:53,911 --> 00:01:58,066
Yeh, we were on the ship and there was this booby trap and well...

26
00:01:58,067 --> 00:02:00,043
...we... we boobied... right into it.

27
00:02:00,044 --> 00:02:05,367
Katara, you shouldn't have gone on that ship. Now we could all be in danger!

28
00:02:05,368 --> 00:02:09,476
Don't blame Katara! I brought her there. It's my fault.

29
00:02:09,477 --> 00:02:13,967
Aha! The traitor confesses! Warriors, away from the enemy!

30
00:02:13,968 --> 00:02:16,831
The foreigner is banned from our village!

31
00:02:16,832 --> 00:02:18,934
Sokka, you're making a mistake.

32
00:02:18,935 --> 00:02:23,396
No! I'm keeping my promise to Dad. I'm protecting you from threats like him!

33
00:02:23,397 --> 00:02:27,384
Aang is not our enemy! Don't you see?

34
00:02:27,385 --> 00:02:31,713
Aang's brought us something we haven't had in a long time. Fun.

35
00:02:31,714 --> 00:02:35,001
Fun? We can't fight firebenders with fun!

36
00:02:35,002 --> 00:02:36,910
You should try it sometime.

37
00:02:36,911 --> 00:02:39,102
Get out of our village. Now!

38
00:02:39,103 --> 00:02:42,505
Grandmother, please, don't let Sokka do this.

39
00:02:42,506 --> 00:02:45,538
Katara, you knew going on that ship was forbidden.

40
00:02:45,539 --> 00:02:49,841
Sokka is right. I think it best if the airbender leaves.

41
00:02:49,842 --> 00:02:52,800
Fine! Then I'm banished too!

42
00:02:52,801 --> 00:02:54,844
C'mon, Aang, let's go!

43
00:02:54,976 --> 00:02:57,176
Where do you think you're going?

44
00:02:57,177 --> 00:03:01,658
To find a waterbender! Aang is taking me to the North Pole!

45
00:03:01,659 --> 00:03:03,613
I am? Great!

46
00:03:03,614 --> 00:03:10,512
Katara! Would you really choose him over your tribe? Your own family?

47
00:03:15,022 --> 00:03:20,373
Katara, I don't want to come between you and your family.

48
00:03:20,374 --> 00:03:25,442
So, you're leaving the South Pole? This is goodbye?

49
00:03:25,443 --> 00:03:27,580
Thanks for penguin sledding with me.

50
00:03:27,581 --> 00:03:28,793
Where will you go?

51
00:03:28,794 --> 00:03:32,374
Guess I'll go back home and look for the airbenders.

52
00:03:32,375 --> 00:03:39,183
Wow, I haven't cleaned my room in a hundred years. Not looking forward to that.

53
00:03:41,159 --> 00:03:43,207
It was nice meeting everyone.

54
00:03:43,208 --> 00:03:46,538
Let's see your bison fly now, air boy.

55
00:03:46,539 --> 00:03:50,658
Come on, Appa, you can do it! Yip! Yip!

56
00:03:52,270 --> 00:03:54,984
Yeh, I thought so.

57
00:03:57,090 --> 00:04:00,057
Aang! Don't go! We'll miss you!

58
00:04:00,058 --> 00:04:02,955
I'll miss you too.

59
00:04:06,886 --> 00:04:09,459
Come on, boy.

60
00:04:17,444 --> 00:04:20,179
Katara, you'll feel better after you...

61
00:04:20,180 --> 00:04:26,133
You happy now? There goes my one chance of becoming a waterbender!

62
00:04:30,306 --> 00:04:31,999
All right! Ready our defenses!

63
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,601
The Fire Nation could be on our shores any moment now!

64
00:04:34,602 --> 00:04:35,249
But, I gotta...

65
00:04:35,250 --> 00:04:38,478
And no potty breaks!

66
00:04:49,473 --> 00:04:53,216
Yeh, I liked her too.

67
00:04:59,836 --> 00:05:02,130
The village!

68
00:05:06,006 --> 00:05:08,523
Appa, wait here!

69
00:06:14,336 --> 00:06:17,409
Oh man!

70
00:06:25,410 --> 00:06:28,310
Ohhh, man!

71
00:06:46,145 --> 00:06:49,588
Sokka, get out of the way!

72
00:08:01,241 --> 00:08:03,984
Where are you hiding him?

73
00:08:10,070 --> 00:08:15,194
He'd be about this age? Master of all elements?

74
00:08:23,158 --> 00:08:26,052
I know you're hiding him!

75
00:08:37,325 --> 00:08:40,739
Show no fear!

76
00:09:26,329 --> 00:09:28,223
Hey Katara. Hey Sokka.

77
00:09:28,224 --> 00:09:32,262
Hi... Aang. Thanks for comin'.

78
00:09:45,811 --> 00:09:47,269
Looking for me?

79
00:09:47,270 --> 00:09:52,540
You're the airbender? You're the Avatar?

80
00:09:52,541 --> 00:09:53,626
Aang?

81
00:09:53,627 --> 00:09:56,335
No way.

82
00:09:56,654 --> 00:09:59,786
I've spent years preparing for this encounter.

83
00:09:59,787 --> 00:10:04,171
Training. Meditating. You're just a child!

84
00:10:04,172 --> 00:10:07,464
Well, you're just a teenager.

85
00:10:20,598 --> 00:10:24,925
If I go with you, will you promise to leave everyone alone?

86
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:36,573
No, Aang! Don't do this!

87
00:10:36,574 --> 00:10:40,642
Don't worry, Katara, it'll be okay.

88
00:10:44,134 --> 00:10:46,803
Take care of Appa for me until I get back.

89
00:10:46,804 --> 00:10:51,596
Head a course to the Fire Nation. I'm going home.

90
00:11:29,595 --> 00:11:31,805
We have to go after that ship, Sokka.

91
00:11:31,806 --> 00:11:34,533
Aang saved our tribe, now we have to save him.

92
00:11:34,534 --> 00:11:35,472
Katara, I...

93
00:11:35,473 --> 00:11:40,254
Why can't you realize that he's on our side? If we don't help him, no one will.

94
00:11:40,255 --> 00:11:42,457
I know you don't like Aang, but we owe him and I...

95
00:11:42,458 --> 00:11:47,722
Katara! Are you gonna talk all day or are you comin' with me?

96
00:11:47,723 --> 00:11:49,960
Sokka!

97
00:11:50,961 --> 00:11:52,950
Get in. We're going to save your boyfriend.

98
00:11:52,951 --> 00:11:53,543
He's not my...

99
00:11:53,544 --> 00:11:54,888
Whatever.

100
00:11:54,889 --> 00:11:58,287
What do you two think you're doing?

101
00:11:59,096 --> 00:12:04,791
You'll need these. You have a long journey ahead of you.

102
00:12:05,999 --> 00:12:09,292
It's been so long since I've had hope.

103
00:12:09,293 --> 00:12:14,201
But you brought it back to life, my little waterbender.

104
00:12:14,569 --> 00:12:19,850
And you, my brave warrior, be nice to your sister.

105
00:12:19,851 --> 00:12:22,681
Yeah... okay, Gran.

106
00:12:22,990 --> 00:12:27,049
Aang is the Avatar. He's the world's only chance.

107
00:12:27,050 --> 00:12:34,722
You both found him for a reason. Now your destinies are intertwined with his.

108
00:12:35,597 --> 00:12:40,205
There's no way we're gonna catch a war ship with a canoe.

109
00:12:42,787 --> 00:12:43,953
Appa!

110
00:12:43,954 --> 00:12:48,549
You just love taking me out of my comfort zone, don't ya?

111
00:12:52,572 --> 00:12:56,122
This staff will make an excellent gift for my father.

112
00:12:56,123 --> 00:13:00,902
I suppose you wouldn't know of fathers, being raised by monks.

113
00:13:00,903 --> 00:13:06,266
Take the Avatar to the prison hold. And take this to my quarters.

114
00:13:06,267 --> 00:13:11,337
Hey, you mind taking this to his quarters for me?

115
00:13:24,823 --> 00:13:28,463
So... I guess you never fought an airbender before.

116
00:13:28,464 --> 00:13:31,795
I bet I can take you both with my hands tied behind my back.

117
00:13:31,796 --> 00:13:33,981
Silence!

118
00:13:52,263 --> 00:13:55,453
The Avatar has escaped!

119
00:14:00,584 --> 00:14:05,689
Go. Fly. Soar.

120
00:14:05,690 --> 00:14:09,010
Please, Appa, we need your help. Aang needs your help.

121
00:14:09,011 --> 00:14:13,917
Up. Ascend. Elevate.

122
00:14:13,918 --> 00:14:17,602
Sokka doesn't believe you can fly, but I do, Appa.

123
00:14:17,603 --> 00:14:21,226
Come on. Don't you wanna save Aang?

124
00:14:22,664 --> 00:14:31,225
What was it that kid said? Yee-ha? Hup hup? Wahoo? Uh... yip yip?

125
00:14:39,620 --> 00:14:41,857
You did it, Sokka!

126
00:14:41,858 --> 00:14:46,636
He's flying! He's flying! Katara, he's...!

127
00:14:47,288 --> 00:14:51,251
I mean, big deal, he's flying.

128
00:15:01,628 --> 00:15:05,451
You haven't seen my staff around, have you?

129
00:15:10,449 --> 00:15:12,090
Thanks anyway!

130
00:15:36,266 --> 00:15:37,949
Sorry...

131
00:15:44,684 --> 00:15:46,645
My staff!

132
00:15:47,124 --> 00:15:50,675
Looks like I underestimated you.

133
00:17:24,740 --> 00:17:27,672
What is that?

134
00:17:29,288 --> 00:17:31,826
Appa!

135
00:17:51,416 --> 00:17:54,685
Aang! No!

136
00:17:55,310 --> 00:18:00,673
Aang! Aang! Aang...!!

137
00:18:26,341 --> 00:18:28,100
Did you see what he just did?

138
00:18:28,101 --> 00:18:32,140
Now that was some waterbending!

139
00:18:39,205 --> 00:18:42,852
Aang! Are you okay?

140
00:18:43,656 --> 00:18:47,916
Hey Katara. Hey Sokka. Thanks for coming.

141
00:18:47,917 --> 00:18:50,441
Well, I couldn't let you have all the glory.

142
00:18:50,442 --> 00:18:51,733
I dropped my staff.

143
00:18:51,734 --> 00:18:53,800
Got it!

144
00:19:04,468 --> 00:19:08,257
Ha! That's from the Water Tribe!

145
00:19:16,977 --> 00:19:19,057
Katara!

146
00:19:29,706 --> 00:19:30,970
Hurry up, Sokka!

147
00:19:30,971 --> 00:19:37,270
I'm just a guy with a boomerang, I didn't ask for all this flying and magic.

148
00:19:37,271 --> 00:19:40,121
Yip yip! Yip yip!

149
00:19:50,694 --> 00:19:53,628
Shoot them down!

150
00:20:17,435 --> 00:20:24,399
Good news for the Fire Lord. The Fire Nation's greatest threat is just a little kid.

151
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:30,065
That kid, Uncle, just did this. I won't underestimate him again.

152
00:20:30,066 --> 00:20:33,722
Dig this ship out and follow them!

153
00:20:35,075 --> 00:20:38,324
As soon as you're done with that.

154
00:20:42,534 --> 00:20:49,165
How did you do that? With the water? It was the most amazing thing I've ever seen.

155
00:20:49,166 --> 00:20:53,017
I don't know. I just sort of... did it.

156
00:20:53,018 --> 00:20:56,429
Why didn't you tell us you were the Avatar?

157
00:20:56,430 --> 00:21:01,250
Because... I never wanted to be.

158
00:21:09,649 --> 00:21:13,210
But Aang, the world's been waiting for the Avatar to return...

159
00:21:13,211 --> 00:21:15,465
...and finally put an end to this war.

160
00:21:15,466 --> 00:21:17,625
And how am I going to do that?

161
00:21:17,626 --> 00:21:22,870
According to legend, you need to first master water, then earth, then fire, right?

162
00:21:22,871 --> 00:21:24,674
That's what the monks told me.

163
00:21:24,675 --> 00:21:28,684
Well, if we go to the North Pole you can master waterbending.

164
00:21:28,685 --> 00:21:30,460
We can learn it together!

165
00:21:30,461 --> 00:21:34,386
And Sokka, I'm sure you'll get to knock some firebender heads on the way.

166
00:21:34,387 --> 00:21:37,730
I'd like that. I'd really like that.

167
00:21:37,731 --> 00:21:39,550
Then we're in this together.

168
00:21:39,551 --> 00:21:41,639
All right, but before I learn waterbending...

169
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:46,828
...we have some serious business to attend to here, here, and here.

170
00:21:46,829 --> 00:21:48,456
What's there?

171
00:21:48,457 --> 00:21:50,487
Here we'll ride the hopping llamas.

172
00:21:50,488 --> 00:21:54,101
Then waaaay over here we'll surf on the backs of giant koi fish.

173
00:21:54,102 --> 00:21:56,851
Then back over here we'll ride the hog-monkeys.

174
00:21:56,852 --> 00:22:01,041
They don't like people riding them, but that's what makes it fun!

175
